      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Benjamin C. Ross (1822-1910), son of Seth (1778-1858) and Hannah (Chapman, ) Ross was a
            farmer and entrepreneur [?] of Onondaga County, NY. He was married to Mary Maria
            (Gumaer) Ross and entered a commercial co-partnership with his brother in law John E.
            Gumaer (Ross &amp; Gumaer). A diploma from August 1885 also lists him as "Special Deputy
            Sheriff [...] for 20 days."</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph>Benjamin C. Ross Papers</emph> comprise financial documents, an indenture and
            a diploma certifying Ross's appointment as deputy sheriff. </p>
      </scopecontent>
